<F P=100> SOUTHERN AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Angola </F>
<H3> <TI>   European Union Sends 500 Tonnes of Foods </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB2201105494 Jamba Voz da Resistencia do Galo Negro in 
Portuguese 0600 GMT 22 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2201105494 </F>
<F P=104>  Jamba Voz da Resistencia do Galo Negro </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Last weekend Caritas received 500 tonnes of 
foodstuffs from the European Union. Caritas Sources say that 
the aid comes at an opportune time and the goods will 
immediately be distributed to the needy population in the 
Luanda, Malanje, Menongue, Huambo, Uige, M'banza Congo and Sumbe 
areas. Meanwhile, Caritas is one of the few humanitarian 
organizations which distributes donations to all Angolans 
without political or ethnical discrimination. Other 
organizations, which claim to be impartial, have been showing 
that their sole aim is to supply areas controlled by the Luanda 
regime. 

</TEXT>

