<F P=100> SOUTHERN AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Lesotho </F>
<H3> <TI>   More Shooting Noted in Maseru 21 Jan; Events Detailed </TI></H3>
<H4>   Troops Attack Defense Headquarters </H4>
<F P=102> MB2301092194 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 0900 GMT 23 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2301092194 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] South Africans have been advised not to travel to 
Maseru or its surrounding areas because of the renewed fighting 
between rival Lesotho military factions which broke out there 
this morning. Diplomats say it is difficult to obtain a clear 
picture of what is happening, but troops from the Makoanyane 
Barracks on the outskirts of the capital are believed to have 
launched an attack on the defense force headquarters in Maseru. 
South African Foreign Minister Pik Botha is being kept well 
informed on the situation. 

</TEXT>

