  [Text] The first independent newspaper in Mozambique, 
SAVANA, is already on the streets. It belongs to Mediacoop, 
proprietors of MEDIAFAX. The weekly newspaper will be on the 
streets every Friday [words indistinct] national project, which 
will try to report on the reality of events in the country, 
without censorship and subterfuge. 
