<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The government has intensified operations against 
illegal arms dealers along the Kenya-Sudan border, the Turkana 
District Commissioner (Simon Mutogwa), has said. He said there 
would be no compromise on matters of Kenyan security and asked 
wananchi [citizens] to report suspected leaders to the police. 
He was reacting to allegations by the Turkana North MP, Mr. 
Japheth Ekidor, who alleged that people from outside the 
district were in Lokichoggio with the intention of buying arms 
from the Sudanese. 

