<H3> <TI>   People's Democratic Movement Renames Organization </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA2501212994 Addis Ababa Voice of Ethiopia Network in 
Amharic 1700 GMT 25 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA2501212994 </F>
<F P=104>  Addis Ababa Voice of Ethiopia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Amharic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Summary] The Ethiopian People's Democratic Movement [EPDM] 
third congress has decided that EPDM, which was struggling under 
the objective of national unity, will continue to struggle under 
the name of ANDM, or Amhara National's Democratic Movement 
[bihere amara demokrasiyawi nikinake] for the interest of the 
Amhara people while upholding its basic democratic principles. 
The congress decided this after assessing the organization's 
yearly development and realizing that it should now shoulder its 
national responsibility, after approving the code of conduct as 
stipulated in the organization's program. 

</TEXT>

