<F P=103> EA2601102794 </F>
<F P=104>  Kampala Radio Uganda Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] The second batch of 168 officers and men of the 
NRA [National Resistance Army] contingent to the ECOMOG 
[Economic Community of West African States Cease-Fire Monitoring 
Group] forces in Liberia left this morning on a chartered flight 
to join their colleagues already in Buchanan. Speaking to the 
troops before their departure at Entebbe International Airport, 
the chief of combat operations, Brigadier Joram Mugume, urged 
them to be good ambassadors of Uganda. He said that the people 
of Uganda expect a successful execution of their peace mission 
with the highest discipline ever. [passage omitted] 
  Today's company, which was drawn from [the] 305th Brigade, 
was led by Major (Sam Lusuba), and this brings the total number 
of NRA troops in Liberia to 338 out of the expected total of 
1,000 troops. 

