<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Suspended PAC Official Clarifies Remarks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB2501190394 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1812 GMT 25 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB2501190394 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Johannesburg Jan 25 SAPA -- Suspended Pan Africanist 
Congress [PAC] National Publicity Director Waters Toboti on 
Tuesday said he had not threatened to unleash chaos if his 
suspension went ahead. Mr Toboti said in a statement to SAPA 
his comments on Radio Transkei earlier on Tuesday were in Xhosa 
and had not been properly translated in subsequent reports. 
"What I said was people who suspend members of the organisation 
on false premises are causing chaos and division in the party." 
  Mr Toboti said he still had not been told of his suspension. 
Earlier, Jaki Seroke of the PAC's publicity and information 
office told SAPA they were having difficulty contacting Mr 
Toboti to tell him of his suspension. 
  On Saturday the PAC announced the suspension of Mr Toboti, 
Central Transkei Regional Secretary Mfanelo Skwatsha and Azanian 
National Youth Unity member Chargin Mabaso with immediate effect 
for criticising the PAC's suspension of its armed struggle. 
  Mr Seroke added the PAC had no interest in getting involved 
in a "slanging match" with Mr Toboti. A decision had been 
taken, he said. 

</TEXT>

