<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Communist Party Notes `Intelligence Networks' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB2501171694 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1400 GMT 25 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2501171694 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The SACP [South African Communist Party] claims that 
the National Party [NP] is using intelligence networks to run a 
smear campaign for electioneering. A member of the SACP Central 
Committee, Mr. Jeremy Cronin, has called on the NP to confirm or 
deny that the SACP's facsimile and telephone lines have been 
tapped. He also called on the NP to explain its connection to 
the National Intelligence Service and to name all the 
Broederbond [Secret Afrikaner Brotherhood] members on its 
election list. 

</TEXT>

