<H3> <TI>   General Document Expected </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB2801123794 Jamba Voz da Resistencia do Galo Negro in 
Portuguese 1200 GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2801123794 </F>
<F P=104>  Jamba Voz da Resistencia do Galo Negro </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Angolans are still hopeful about the outcome of the 
Lusaka talks between the National Union for the Total 
Independence of Angola [UNITA] and the Luanda regime. Angolans, 
as a whole, long for peace. 
  Meanwhile, diplomatic sources following the talks say the 
proceedings continue today with the discussion of the final 
aspects on the formation of the new national police force. 
Yesterday, the sides agreed on specific issues. The sources 
stressed that the two sides regard as possible the approval of 
the general document on the second round of talks. It has been 
suggested that the delegations are committed to establishing a 
just peace for Angola, despite the military operations carried 
out by the Luanda regime with the backing of one of the 
observers to he peace process. This has created a great deal of 
confusion about Russian's role in the ongoing talks. 

</TEXT>

