<F P=100> SOUTHERN AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Lesotho </F>
<H3> <TI>   Envoys From Botswana, RSA, Zimbabwe Arrive in Maseru </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB2801121594 Maseru Radio Lesotho in English 1130 GMT 28 Jan 
94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2801121594 </F>
<F P=104>  Maseru Radio Lesotho </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A team of 17 envoys from Botswana, South Africa, and 
Zimbabwe arrived in Maseru this morning at the beginning of a 
three-day fact finding mission in Lesotho regarding the tense 
security situation in the country. During their stay the team 
will meet with the government, leaders of political parties, and 
other leaders. At the end of their stay in Lesotho, they will 
report their findings to their countries who will consider how 
they can assist Lesotho in finding a peaceful solution to its 
present tense security situation. 

</TEXT>

