<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The British minister of state for foreign and 
commonwealth affairs and minister for overseas development, 
Baroness Lynda Chalker, arrived in the country today for a 
two-day official visit to Malawi. During the visit, Baroness 
Chalker will hold discussions with His Excellency The President 
Ngwazi [paramount] Dr. Kamuzu Banda as well as political leaders 
from both the ruling and opposition parties. She will also meet 
members of the National Consultative Committee, among other 
(?leaders). 
  Speaking to newsmen on arrival in Lilongwe, Baroness Chalker 
welcomed changes that are taking place in Malawi [word 
indistinct]. She said it was important that the progress that 
has been achieved so far should be maintained. Baroness Chalker 
noted that her government has already contributed $300,000 
through the United Nations to assist in Malawi's forthcoming 
general election. She added that she will be discussing further 
[words indistinct] with the Malawi Government. 

