<F P=100> SOUTHERN AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Mozambique </F>
<H3> <TI>   UN Representative Notes Imbalances in Troop Confinement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB2801093294 Maputo Radio Mozambique Network in Portuguese 
0400 GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2801093294 </F>
<F P=104>  Maputo Radio Mozambique Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The UN Secretary General's representative Aldo 
Ajello has said in Maputo that there is an imbalance in the 
confinement of troops. Ajello said the Mozambique National 
Resistance has used more than 70 percent of its assembly areas, 
while the government has used 30 to 35 percent. At its meeting 
in Maputo on 27 January, the Supervision and Control Commission 
recommended that the government speed up the confinement of its 
troops and pledged the necessary logistical assistance to speed 
up the process. 
  Minister Armando Guebuza said the government has not sent 
sufficient troops to specific assembly areas because the latter 
lack the technical capacity to accommodate people. He said 
several areas face food problems, adding that a number of 
technical units cannot register more than 50 people. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

