<H3> <TI>   Presidential Motorcade Pelted in Western Province </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB2801090994 Lusaka Zambia National Broadcasting Corporation 
Network in English 0500 GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2801090994 </F>
<F P=104>  Lusaka Zambia National Broadcasting Corporation 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The United Democratic Party [UDP] has condemned the 
pelting of the presidential motorcade by the people of Western 
Province. UDP interim national chairman Mr. (Kapemba Phiri) 
said it was wrong for people in Mongu to behave in such a 
manner. He said the president should be respected regardless of 
which party he belonged to, and urged all leaders to discipline 
their members. The motorcade was pelted with stones and mangoes 
when President Chiluba went there to campaign for the Mongu 
Central by-election. 

