<H3> <TI>   U.S. Embassy Staff Member Escapes Injury During Shooting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA2701173394 Addis Ababa Voice of Ethiopia in Amharic to 
Neighboring Countries 1600 GMT 27 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA2701173394 </F>
<F P=104>  Addis Ababa Voice of Ethiopia </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Amharic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] The Addis Ababa police today reported that 
unidentified gunmen fired three times at an American Embassy 
staff member while the diplomat was returning towards town from 
the Bole US AID offices. The police added that the embassy 
staff member who was attacked escaped unhurt, and that the 
criminals have not yet been apprehended. The police also noted 
that the shooting came from a Toyota Land Cruiser which was 
identical in make and color to the one belonging to the American 
Embassy staff member, had a diplomatic corps registration number 
of 04 Addis Ababa 60, and approached the left-hand side of the 
embassy staff member's car. Two of the three bullets fired 
penetrated the driver's door, and the two vehicles collided as a 
result. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

