<F P=101> Nigeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Orders End to Arrest of Former Legislators </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AB2801121594 Kaduna Radio Nigeria in English 0900 GMT 28 Jan 
94 </F>

<F P=103> AB2801121594 </F>
<F P=104>  Kaduna Radio Nigeria </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] State governments have been asked to stop further 
arrest and detention of legislators under the last civilian 
administration. A statement from the office of the chief of 
general staff says the legislators could be allowed to repay the 
loans in accordance with the terms of payment entered into when 
such loans were obtained. The government also directed 
administrators to ensure that public funds were no longer 
deposited with finance houses. Instead central banks should be 
used for that purpose. 
  Meanwhile, deposits by prospective candidates for the 
abortive 1993 local government elections are to be refunded. A 
directive to that effect from the presidency in Abuja asked 
state administrators to ascertain the amount the politicians 
spent on the abortive elections and where the money was 
deposited. They are also to identify bona fide candidates and 
make arrangements for their refund. 

</TEXT>

