<H3> <TI>   Anhui Province Develops Telecom Networks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW3012161693 Beijing XINHUA in English 1427 GMT 30 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> OW3012161693 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hefei, December 30 (XINHUA) -- Program-controlled 
and mobile telephone networks now cover every city and county in 
east China's Anhui Province. 
  The province has invested 1.3 billion yuan to build program- 
controlled telephone switches, optical cables and microwave 
relay stations this year. It has developed several 
telecommunications networks, of both cable type and wireless 
type. 
  Now the province has 660,000 automatic telephone terminals 
which are connected to international networks, a digital 
info-transmission network and a 900 kilohertz mobile telephone 
network which enables people to call from anywhere in the 
province with a wireless telephone. 

</TEXT>

