Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporter Gao Haorong (7559 3185 2837)] </F>
  [Text] Pyongyang, 28 Dec (XINHUA) -- Kim Yong-nam, DPRK 
vice premier and minister of foreign affairs, stressed today 
that the people of Korea and China should jointly strive to 
develop the Korean-Chinese friendship established by the two 
countries' leaders. 
  Speaking at a new year reception hosted by Qiao Zonghuai, 
Chinese ambassador to the DPRK, Kim Yong-nam said: On the 
occasion when the Chinese people are solemnly marking the birth 
centenary of Comrade Mao Zedong, the Korean people also deeply 
